Valgrind - double free()

1,	void	free_str(char *str)
	{
		free(str);
		str = NULL;
	}

	If you pass char* by value, str = NULL only within the scope of this function.
	The variable 'var' that passed value in the calling function will not be NULL.
	Assume var was already freed. 	
	If you did something like, if (var != NULL) {free (var);}
	var would not be equal to NULL, thus you could attempt to free var again.

2,	solution. pass by reference.
	void	free_str(char **str)

3,	same applies for 2D array.
	void	free_dbl_arr(char ***dbl_arr)
	
		while((*dbl_arr)[i] != NULL) 	// loop condition
			free((*dbl_arr)[i]);			// free str at array index i
			(*dbl_arr)[i] = NULL; 		// set str at array index i to NULL

		finally set the pointer to the array of strings to NULL
		*dbl_arr = NULL;
